cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CL

The paper deals with the application of machine learning techniques, specifically convolutional neural networks, for detecting bird sounds in audio recordings. This falls under the domain of signal processing and audio analysis, which is covered by cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). The use of deep learning models for this task also suggests the involvement of computer vision techniques, which is covered by cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper involves data augmentation and ensemble methods, which are common techniques in machine learning and could be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of natural language processing techniques for the task of bird sound detection, which could be classified under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper involves the use of large datasets and the evaluation of model performance, which could be classified under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
